properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 5 at 5:52AM CST until January 5 at 4:00PM CST by NWS Des Moines IA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northwest winds 20 to 30 mph with a few gusts up to 45
mph expected.The strongest winds will occur between 8 AM and
noon.

* WHERE....Portions of west central Iowa.

* WHEN...From 8 AM this morning to 4 PM CST this afternoon. The
strongest winds will occur between 8 AM and noon.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects.
High profile vehicles on north/south roadways will be impacted.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 PM CST THIS AFTERNOON
